# Cursor Rules

This project uses **superpower-with-files (SPF)** for AI-assisted development.

## Plan Management

Use these commands to track and manage development plans:

| Command                  | Action                          |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------- |
| `/spf list`              | List all plans with status      |
| `/spf status <project>`  | Detailed plan status            |
| `/spf resume <project>`  | Resume execution                |
| `/spf block <project>`   | Mark as blocked                 |
| `/spf unblock <project>` | Remove blocked status           |
| `/spf complete <project>`| Mark complete                   |

## Quick Examples

**List plans:**
```
User: "show me my plans"
Agent: Lists all plans from .superpower-with-files/_registry/PLANS.md
```

**Check status:**
```
User: "status of nautilus-trader"
Agent: Shows phase progress, tasks completed, next steps
```

**Resume work:**
```
User: "resume nautilus-trader"
Agent: Loads context and invokes spf-exec-plan
```

## File Structure

```
.superpower-with-files/
├── _registry/PLANS.md       # Plan index
├── {project}/
│   ├── task_plan.md         # Phases
│   ├── active_tdd_plan.md   # Tasks
│   └── progress.md          # Log
```

## Key Skills

- `spf-plan-manager` - Plan tracking
- `spf-write-plan` - Create plans
- `spf-exec-plan` - Execute plans
- `test-driven-development` - TDD workflow
